HEADWORD: Excito-nutrient
<hw>Ex*ci`to-nu"tri*ent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>Exciting nutrition; said of the reflex
influence by which the nutritional processes are either excited or
modified.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Excito-secretory</ent>⟦br⟧
